  <md:abstract><para>By the end of this section, you will be able to:</para>
<list>
<item>Express the state of an electron in a hydrogen atom in terms of five quantum numbers</item>
<item>Use quantum numbers to calculate the magnitude and direction of the spin and magnetic moment of an electron</item>
<item>Explain the fine and hyperfine structure of the hydrogen spectrum in terms of magnetic interactions inside the hydrogen atom</item>
</list></md:abstract>
